HEADWORD: Hilly
<hw>Hill"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Abounding
with hills; uneven in surface; <as>as, a <ex>hilly</ex>
country</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Hilly</xex> steep.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Lofty; <as>as, <ex>hilly</ex> empire</as>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

